Sometimes you just need pull out progress pics and compare…
.
Last checkin I felt puffy (time of month didn’t help) and like I am just not making any progress 😅 We all have those days, where we all lack motivation at times but discipline and staying consistent WILL always pay off in the end! 
.
Left Pic- 2018 Competing Bikini, always trying to keep muscle under control, lighter weights, eating to stay smaller, having to do lots of cardio on prep to look less muscular 🥹 : NOTE this is Deep in Prep and the smallest I have ever weighed 
.
Right Pic- last week Competing Wellness, working on growing muscle, eating to grow (not tracking food) but EATING, cardio maybe 20 min 2 days a week, lifting HEAVY, doing what I love, working with my body!
NOTE this is off season and the most I have ever weighed 
.
If I remember correctly this is about a 20lb difference here 😅🍑 
.
Growth takes Time, Patience, and Consistency

Client Love ❤️ down 10lbs in 3 months.
.
Been working with @ky_hayes2 for 3 months now and she is a pretty dope momma of an adorable little girl! 
.
In the past 3 months I have just been working on consistency with her. Trying to tighten up without compromising any of her beautiful shape and size she has.
.
No changes to the food, no changes to the workouts, just working on getting in the groove of a new routine and learning to be consistent over perfection. 
.
Each week focusing on maybe 1-3 goals NOT 10! Little by little getting more consistent day by day and it’s paying off 👏 
.
She has been doing great things and is down 10lbs since January 👏

A Quick 30 minutes on Zoom can make some Big difference.

Client Spotlight… 14 days in!
NO WEIGHT CHANGE 150lbs in each. 
Don’t fixate on the scale, that’s a relationship you can give up right now 😅 because it won’t serve you. Use it as a tool not the goal. 
.
Before she came to me she was previously doing 60 min cardio first then weight training, no training plan, working out 6,7 days a week. 
.
What I did the last 14 days. Cut her cardio to 20 min post workout, feeding her body with the correct foods, weight training 5 days a week, and 2 full rest days for recovery. 
.
Learning to work with the body and not against it and I am so happy to see where this is going 👏
